title: doc: Go 1.7 release notes missing 'unordered examples' change
body:
The release notes for Go 1.7 say:

>go/doc
>
>  To support the corresponding change in go test described above, Example struct adds a Unordered field indicating whether the example may generate its output lines in any order.

...but no corresponding change is mentioned above. I assume it is referring to https://golang.org/cl/19280/.
